## Proposed Changes

### Component 1: Supabase Branch — Health Data Isolation

> [!IMPORTANT]
> Health data lives in a **dedicated Supabase branch**, not co-mingled with Chorum's core tables. The branch gets copies of the auth and core tables it needs (users, learnings, learning_scopes, embeddings) but health-specific tables are isolated.

#### Tables in health branch

| Table | Purpose |
|-------|---------|
| `health_snapshots` | Append-only AES-256-GCM encrypted health records (labs, Garmin daily, ICD reports, vitals, MyChart docs) |
| `health_sources` | Trusted medical knowledge source registry (Mayo, Cleveland Clinic, NIH, NHS, etc.) |
| `phi_audit_log` | HIPAA-required access log — every view, create, export, decrypt, delete |
| `garmin_sync_state` | Encrypted OAuth tokens + sync cursor for server-side Garmin HRV |
| (copied) `learnings` | Health-scoped learnings synced from/to Chorum core |
| (copied) `learning_scopes` | Scope tags for health learnings (`#health`, `#cardiac`, `#labs`, etc.) |

#### Health learning types added to `LearningType`

```
health_metric      — extracted vital/metric with value + reference range
health_trend       — detected pattern across multiple snapshots
health_alert       — flagged anomaly or out-of-range value
health_baseline    — established normal ranges for this user
```

