### Component 10: HIPAA Hardening

| Safeguard | Implementation |
|-----------|---------------|
| Encryption at rest | AES-256-GCM for all PHI in `health_snapshots` |
| Encryption in transit | HTTPS/TLS 1.3 (Vercel enforced) |
| Access control | Google OAuth + Supabase Auth + ownership checks |
| Audit logging | `phi_audit_log` — every PHI access logged with user, IP, timestamp |
| Auto-logoff | 15-min idle (web), biometric re-auth (mobile) |
| De-identification | PHI scrubbing before LLM injection — clinical values only, never PII |
| Rate limiting | 600/min on MCP (existing), additional limits on health routes |
| Data integrity | SHA-256 hash per snapshot, append-only (no overwrites/deletes) |
| Isolation | Dedicated Supabase branch — health tables separated from core |

